  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/jellyfish-hr.jpg
  video: ./src/assets/videos/jellyfish-1.mp4
intro:
  title: The problem is not technology, data quality, or even lack of budget or business cases. It’s the **complexity of combining all these elements together into solutions that deliver ROI**.
  content_left: |-
    Your systems work. Your teams work. Your data exists.
    But together, they don’t translate into measurable impact.

    The problem isn’t individual systems. It’s misaligned priorities across disconnected initiatives that waste investment.
  content_right: |-
    - Investments in data and AI that don’t pay off
    - ERP, CRM, and operational systems aren’t truly integrated
    - Metrics are defined differently across systems and teams
highlight_one:
  title: We make your data, technology, metrics, and AI work as one.
  subtitle: |-
    by starting with the decisions your business needs to make, and aligning business and technology around them.

    We design your data platform, systems, and models as one connected foundation, preventing fragmented initiatives and wasted investment.
highlight_two:
  title1: The Goal?
  title2: Establish a single, trusted view of the business, where decisions, data, and outcomes are aligned.
  content: |-
    We replace fragmented architectures and conflicting logic with a connected data foundation that keeps systems, metrics, and decisions aligned.

    So you can move faster, trust what you see, and scale both analytics and AI with confidence.
foundations_titles:
  title1: The impact on
  title2: your business
foundations_elements:
  - title: Connected data system
    content: Your systems, pipelines, and data models are integrated into one consistent structure.
  - title: Metrics everyone trusts
    content: Definitions are standardized and embedded into your data platform, not recreated in every tool.
  - title: AI that delivers value
    content: Built on governed, structured data with clear lineage and explainability.
  - title: Faster, more confident decisions
    content: Insights are embedded into workflows and systems, not isolated in dashboards.
  - title: A foundation that scales with you
    content: As your business grows, your data and systems grow with it, without breaking or losing consistency.
about:
  title: Who We Are
  content: |-
    We’re not just data engineers or consultants. We’ve sat on **both sides**.

    We combine experience across data platform architecture, analytics, finance, operations, and large-scale transformation programs.

    We understand how systems behave in reality, and how business decisions depend on them.

    That’s why we focus on what most projects miss: **how data, systems, and decisions connect in reality.**

    Our approach is simple: **design it properly, build it properly, and make sure it delivers measurable outcomes.**
whyus_intro:
  title: What’s Holding You Back
  content: Enterprises are drowning in data, but struggling to turn it into performance.
whyus_elements:
  - title: Decisions feel slower than they should
    content: By the time you get clarity, the moment to act has already passed.
  - title: No consistent view of the business
    content: Different systems, pipelines, and teams produce conflicting answers to the same questions.
  - title: Too much time spent fixing instead of analyzing
    content: Teams spend more time reconciling data than using it to drive performance.
  - title: Limited trust in data and reporting
    content: If numbers aren’t traceable through systems and transformations, they’re hard to rely on.
  - title: Systems that don’t truly work together
    content: Integrations exist, but the underlying architecture is fragmented and inconsistent.
  - title: Data pipelines that are fragile and hard to evolve
    content: Logic is scattered across tools and code, making changes slow, risky, and expensive.
  - title: No clear visibility into how data flows and breaks
    content: When something goes wrong, it’s hard to detect, trace, and fix quickly.
  - title: Business logic spread across systems and people
    content: Critical definitions live in spreadsheets, dashboards, and individual knowledge rather than in one place.
  - title: AI that never moves beyond experiments
    content: Without structured, governed data and stable pipelines, production AI remains out of reach.
  - title: Growing pressure on unstable foundations
    content: More data, faster reporting, and higher expectations built on systems that weren’t designed to support them.
our_services:
  title: How We Deliver Results
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-dyvenia26.jpg
our_services_items:
  - title: Engineering
